-- New York Jets Hire Miami Dolphins’ DeGuglielmo as Offensive Line Coach
-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 2012-01-24T22:20:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/new-york-jets-hire-miami-dolphins-deguglielmo-as-offensive-line-coach.html
The  New York Jets  hired former Miami
Dolphins assistant Dave DeGuglielmo as their offensive line
coach, the team said in a news release.  DeGuglielmo was Miami’s offensive line coach from 2009-2011
when Jets offensive coordinator  Tony Sparano  was head coach of
the Dolphins.  DeGuglielmo also has worked as a coach for the  New York
Giants , the University of  South Carolina  and  Boston College . He
played for  Boston University  from 1987-90 when Sparano was
offensive line coach there.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  